                {
                    "id": "fe_mn_synergy_heatmap",
                    "description": "Joint dependence of the synergistic oxidation rate on both transition metals: a Cartesian sweep of dissolved Mn(II) and Fe(III), each from 1.0e-5 to 1.0e-2 mol/m^3 logarithmically, with S(IV) held at its 1 µM default. R_synergy_term = k_FeMn·[Mn(II)]·[Fe(III)]·[S(IV)] is proportional to the product of the two metal concentrations, so the heatmap rises toward the upper-right corner where both metals are abundant — the Fe/Mn synergism of Eq. 7.102.",
